### Casual Interactive Post Formula (Discussion Style)

**IMPORTANT: Product Hunt moderation requires posts to be community-focused, not promotional. Use this human, conversational style:**

```
Title: "[Question that invites discussion]" or "Am I the only one who [relatable frustration]?"

Body Structure:
[Personal Story - Natural, Conversational]
Opening with personal context (e.g., "Okay, weird thought that's been bugging me...")
Share a specific frustration or observation
Use natural language, not bullet points

[Reflection - Why This Matters]
Connect to broader patterns
Use conversational transitions ("Here's what really got me:", "I feel like...")
Show vulnerability ("I can't quite put my finger on what it is")

[Optional: Mention Product as Example, NOT Promotion]
If mentioning a product (including yours):
- Frame as discovery: "I stumbled on this thing called X recently"
- Describe neutrally: "they have this interesting approach where..."
- Show genuine reaction: "It felt refreshingly simple, honestly"
- NEVER use promotional language like "Check it out" or "We built"

[Open-Ended Questions - Invite Discussion]
Ask 2-3 genuine questions
Use natural phrasing: "Has anyone else felt this?"
Show uncertainty: "Or am I just being impatient?"
Encourage different perspectives: "If this is a solved problem, please call me out!"

TONE: Natural, human, vulnerable, curious
AVOID: Lists, bullet points, promotional CTAs, structured sections
GOAL: Start a real conversation, not promote a product
```

